<paragraph blockId="8.[192,654,834,891]" box="[192,362,867,891]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">
(
<figureCitation box="[200,353,867,891]" captionStart="Figure 70-80" captionStartId="19.[192,276,1836,1858]" captionTargetBox="[229,1396,229,1776]" captionTargetId="figure-19@19.[223,1405,192,1808]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 70-80. Hyperaspis drechseli. 70-73) Habitus views. 74) Abdomen. 75-79) Male genitalia. 75) Sipho. 75) Enlarged siphonal apex. 77-78) Lateral and ventral views of phallobase. 79) Enlarged view of basal lobe. 80) Antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5160430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5160430/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Figure 70-80</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[192,1441,931,1627]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,354,931,955]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Description</emphasis>
. Male 
<typeStatus box="[434,542,931,955]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">holotype</typeStatus>
. Length 
<quantity box="[645,737,931,955]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="2.1">2.1 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity box="[823,917,931,955]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.6 mm</quantity>
. Body rounded, convex. Dorsal surface with head alutaceous, slightly shiny, pronotum slightly alutaceous, shiny, elytron smooth, shiny. Color black except head yellow; pronotum yellow with large, basomedian black macula extended 5/6 distance to apical pronotal border, macula not reaching lateral border, anterolateral angle emarginated with yellow; elytron black with lateral and apical margins narrowly yellow, yellow apical border widened (
<figureCitation box="[1169,1287,1059,1083]" captionStart="Figure 70-80" captionStartId="19.[192,276,1836,1858]" captionTargetBox="[229,1396,229,1776]" captionTargetId="figure-19@19.[223,1405,192,1808]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 70-80. Hyperaspis drechseli. 70-73) Habitus views. 74) Abdomen. 75-79) Male genitalia. 75) Sipho. 75) Enlarged siphonal apex. 77-78) Lateral and ventral views of phallobase. 79) Enlarged view of basal lobe. 80) Antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5160430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5160430/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Fig. 70-73</figureCitation>
); propleuron, epipleuron, legs yellow; abdomen dark brown with narrow lateral and apical border yellow. Head punctures small, nearly invisible, separated by less than to 3 times a diameter; pronotal punctures larger than on head, separated by less than to a diameter; elytral punctures larger than on pronotum, separated by less than to twice a diameter; punctures on metaventrite larger than on elytron, separated by about a diameter, becoming coarser laterally, contiguous or nearly so; punctures on basal abdominal ventrite small medially, separated by less than to twice a diameter, punctures on ventrites 2-6 fine, separated by about twice a diameter. Clypeal apex deeply emarginate, clypeus and frons joined at abrupt angle. Epipleuron narrow, slightly grooved medially, slightly descending externally, femoral depresssions deep. Antenna with 11 articles (
<figureCitation box="[393,479,1347,1371]" captionStart="Figure 70-80" captionStartId="19.[192,276,1836,1858]" captionTargetBox="[229,1396,229,1776]" captionTargetId="figure-19@19.[223,1405,192,1808]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 70-80. Hyperaspis drechseli. 70-73) Habitus views. 74) Abdomen. 75-79) Male genitalia. 75) Sipho. 75) Enlarged siphonal apex. 77-78) Lateral and ventral views of phallobase. 79) Enlarged view of basal lobe. 80) Antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5160430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5160430/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Fig. 80</figureCitation>
). Protibia narrow, not flanged. Prosternum with intercoxal carinae widely separated at apex, strongly convergent toward base, joined just before base, connected to base by single stem. Postcoxal line on basal abdominal ventrite arcuate, slightly flattened in median 1/3 along posterior margin of ventrite, rounded 7/8 distance to lateral margin (
<figureCitation box="[854,940,1443,1467]" captionStart="Figure 70-80" captionStartId="19.[192,276,1836,1858]" captionTargetBox="[229,1396,229,1776]" captionTargetId="figure-19@19.[223,1405,192,1808]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 70-80. Hyperaspis drechseli. 70-73) Habitus views. 74) Abdomen. 75-79) Male genitalia. 75) Sipho. 75) Enlarged siphonal apex. 77-78) Lateral and ventral views of phallobase. 79) Enlarged view of basal lobe. 80) Antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5160430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5160430/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Fig. 74</figureCitation>
). Fifth ventrite broadly, weakly emarginate apically; 6 
<superScript attach="left" box="[354,369,1473,1487]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">th</superScript>
ventrite broadly emarginate apically. Genitalia with basal lobe nearly as long as paramere, weakly sinuate, apex rounded, with rounded lateral projection; paramere slender, basal 2/3 wider than apical 1/3, apex ventrally hooked (
<figureCitation box="[608,734,1539,1563]" captionStart="Figure 70-80" captionStartId="19.[192,276,1836,1858]" captionTargetBox="[229,1396,229,1776]" captionTargetId="figure-19@19.[223,1405,192,1808]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 70-80. Hyperaspis drechseli. 70-73) Habitus views. 74) Abdomen. 75-79) Male genitalia. 75) Sipho. 75) Enlarged siphonal apex. 77-78) Lateral and ventral views of phallobase. 79) Enlarged view of basal lobe. 80) Antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5160430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5160430/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Fig. 77-79</figureCitation>
); sipho long, slender, with apical membranous area, basal capsule with inner arm long, straight, apically knobbed, outer arm short, wide, basal border weakly emarginate (
<figureCitation box="[349,479,1603,1627]" captionStart="Figure 70-80" captionStartId="19.[192,276,1836,1858]" captionTargetBox="[229,1396,229,1776]" captionTargetId="figure-19@19.[223,1405,192,1808]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 70-80. Hyperaspis drechseli. 70-73) Habitus views. 74) Abdomen. 75-79) Male genitalia. 75) Sipho. 75) Enlarged siphonal apex. 77-78) Lateral and ventral views of phallobase. 79) Enlarged view of basal lobe. 80) Antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5160430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5160430/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Fig. 75, 76</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[192,448,1667,1691]" box="[192,448,1667,1691]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,293,1667,1691]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Female</emphasis>
. Not known.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
