<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[192,1440,1827,1915]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,315,1827,1851]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gordon &amp; González" authorityYear="2011" box="[328,579,1827,1851]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Hyperaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="drechseli">
<emphasis box="[328,579,1827,1851]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Hyperaspis drechseli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a color pattern similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Gordon and Canepari" authorityName="Gordon and Canepari" box="[1020,1439,1827,1851]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Hyperaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uninotata">
<emphasis box="[1020,1042,1828,1851]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1055,1174,1828,1851]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">uninotata</emphasis>
Gordon and Canepari
</taxonomicName>
to which it goes in the key to species, couplet 
<quantity box="[731,791,1859,1883]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.144" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" unit="in" value="36.0">36 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Gordon, R. D. &amp; C. Canepari" box="[796,1144,1859,1883]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" pagination="245 - 512" refId="ref7630" refString="Gordon, R. D., and C. Canepari. 2008. South American Coccinellidae (Coleoptera), Part XI: a systematic revision of Hyperaspidini (Hyperaspidinae). Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale &quot; G. Doria &quot; XCIX: 245 - 512." type="book chapter" year="2008">Gordon and Canepari (2008)</bibRefCitation>
, but 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gordon &amp; González" authorityYear="2011" box="[1201,1346,1859,1883]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Hyperaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="drechseli">
<emphasis box="[1201,1223,1860,1883]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1236,1346,1859,1883]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">drechseli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the outer elytral ring of yellow only on the lateral and/or apical borders, while 
<taxonomicName box="[1085,1240,1892,1915]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Hyperaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uninotata">
<emphasis box="[1085,1107,1892,1915]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1120,1240,1892,1915]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">uninotata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the anterior
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[192,1440,195,252]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
border also yellow. Another similar species is 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gordon &amp; González" authorityYear="2011" box="[726,914,195,219]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Hyperaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unimaculosa">
<emphasis box="[726,748,196,219]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[760,914,195,219]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">unimaculosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, described above, but 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gordon &amp; González" authorityYear="2011" box="[1171,1312,195,219]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Hyperaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="drechseli">
<emphasis box="[1171,1193,196,219]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1205,1312,195,219]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">drechseli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is smaller, has the male 6 
<superScript attach="left" box="[367,382,225,239]" fontSize="6" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">th</superScript>
ventrite distinctly emarginate apically, and very different male genitalia.
</paragraph>
